Two people were killed and three others injured one critically when a large waste removal truck overturned on Soutpansberg Road in Kempton Park on the East Rand on Saturday paramedics said.ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said ER24 paramedics had arrived on the scene shortly after 3pm on Saturday afternoon to find the truck lying on its side next to the road. One person from the truck was found lying at the back. He had sustained severe traumatic injuries. Sadly there was nothing that paramedics could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene. Upon further assessment paramedics found two people trapped halfway under the truck near the cabin. One of them was found with fatal injuries and declared dead Vermaak said.The other person was in a critical condition. Paramedics were unable to remove him from underneath the truck and a large towing vehicle was called to the scene to partially lift the truck to free him. Once freed paramedics found that he sustained severe traumatic injuries. He was later placed on life support and a medical helicopter was called to the scene to airlift him to hospital. Rescue workers struggled for over an hour to free the trapped man Vermaak said. Two other workers were found near the truck with moderate injuries. They were assessed treated and transported to a nearby hospital. The exact cause of the incident is not yet known. Local authorities attended the scene and will conduct an investigation. 